In a statement, President Obama commemorates Juneteenth, the day in 1865 when word reached Galveston, Texas that slaves there were free. He acknowledges that while this marked an important moment in the nation's history, it was just the beginning of a long struggle for equal rights and treatment. The President also mentions the 50th Anniversary of Freedom Summer and honors those who fought for equality and opportunity for all Americans. He emphasizes the ongoing work of perfecting the Union.